eration mode are motivated by the rapidly evolving landscape in the industry and the intellectual environment at stanford in particular as the magnetic recording industry prospers and matures new industries are emerging most notably in spintronics and biomagnetics we envision that our center should be positioned to effect or lead new waves of magnetics based technologies before the emerging technologies blossom into mainstream industries faculty memberships 10k dollars per year company receives reprints and preprints of technical articles and theses is entitled to send one staff member to the annual program review and center organized workshops and is assigned a stanford faculty member as liaison a nanopatterning initiative focusing on bit patterned media and discrete track recording is being launched by the center in 2007 2008 the membership level to this initiative is set at 100k dollars per year direct sponsored projects student fellowships and equipment donation to the center and center affiliated faculty are also welcome and can be arranged on a case by case basis last modified wed 25 jan 2012 at 13 53 find a lab or organization stay connected itunes icon google+ icon facebook icon twitter icon linkedin icon stanford university school of engineering 475 via ortega stanford california 94305 4121 650.725 1575 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved accreditation info terms of use copyright complaints contact us
